node.text: The new album is named for West’s late mother, who passed away in 2007. While DONDA explores a wider range of genres than his previous album Jesus is King, it features some of the religious themes that West has pivoted to in his recent music. A partial tracklist posted by West ahead of the release listed titles like “Pure Souls” and “Keep My Spirit Alive.” The album will be available for purchase and streaming on July 23rd.

node.text: Founded by Jeff Bezos, space travel company Blue Origin completed its first passenger flight on July 20. The rocket, named New Shepard, carried Bezos and three other passengers more than 65-miles above Earth, just to the boundary of space, known as the Kármán line. Watch our latest episode of HBNN to learn more.

node.title: @jeffbezos Completes His First Flight into Space

node.text:
@hypeart: Paris‘ iconic L’Arc de Triomphe monument is currently being wrapped for an art project that has been 60 years in the making. 'L’Arc de Triomphe, Wrapped' was the brain-child of late artist couple, Christo and Jeanne-Claude, who have given full clearance in their will to have their team continue to work on this project past their death. Hit the link in bio to watch the live stream. ⁠
Photo: André Grossmann/Christo and Jeanne-Claude Foundation

@nasa announced earlier this week that an asteroid the size of the Empire State Building will fly dangerously close to Earth sometime in the 2100s. Named Bennu, the asteroid has a 1-in-1,750 chance of hitting our planet with its trajectory expected to get unclear in the year 2135 to 2182. Learn more via the link in bio.⁠
Photo: NASA/Goddard/University of Arizona

@hypeart: The City of Sin will soon play host to one of the largest auctions of Picasso paintings ever. Presented by @sothebys, 11 works owned by the @mgmresortsintl, with a combined estimated value at around $100 million USD, will be available for the biggest pocketbook on October 23 at the Bellagio. Head to the link in bio to learn more about the artworks heading for sale. ⁠⁠

@hypebeastkicks: @nike is already gearing up for the winter months with its upcoming Air Force 1 Low in "Off Noir." The simple colorway is constructed of premium suede, tonal Swoosh, with hints of brown along the "Nike Air" branding as it sits atop a dark chocolate midsole. Expect these to release soon for $110 USD.⁠

#hypeAF: @tacobell is upgrading its dining experience to the next level with its “Taco Bell Defy” restaurant. The 3,000 square-foot restaurant concept located in Brooklyn Park, Minnesota, utilizes a two-story model for “the frictionless future of Taco Bell.” The concept designed for digital consumers combines technology and unique design elements, to disrupt conventions and maximize ease. Other highlights include multiple drive-thru lanes, a proprietary contactless lift system, and more.⁠⁠
Photo: Taco Bell

@hypebeastkicks: @thesimpsons and @adidasoriginals are continuing their partnership with a new take on the McCarten, inspired by Springfield’s most famous left-hander: Ned Flanders. Dubbed “Left-Handers Rule,” the sneaker sports a predominantly brown suede build that dresses the toebox, collar, tongue, heel, and mudguard. A green leather panel matches Flanders' signature sweater, while pink trim on the collar nod to the character's signature bright shirt. Expect these to arrive on October 3.⁠⁠
Photo: Simpsons, adidas UK
